# burnrate runs fully offline with no .env at all: the LLM routing chain falls
# through to a deterministic incident drafter, and background tasks run inline when
# Redis is absent — so every number reproduces with zero keys and zero cost. Set
# any of these to route incident summaries to a real model or defer tasks onto
# Redis. NEVER commit real keys; on a public host leave them unset (offline).

# --- Routing mode -----------------------------------------------------------
# auto (default) walks the full chain; or pin a tier: paid | local | free | offline
# LLM_MODE=auto

# --- Paid providers (tried first in auto) -----------------------------------
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your-key-here
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5-20251001
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-key-here
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini

# --- Local Ollama (autodetected via /api/tags; cost $0) ---------------------
# OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434
# OLLAMA_MODEL=llama3.1:8b

# --- Free providers (OpenRouter free-tier models) ---------------------------
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-your-key-here
# OPENROUTER_MODEL=google/gemma-4-31b-it:free

# --- Background tasks (TaskTiger / Redis) ------------------------------------
# Redis enables the deferred TaskTiger-shaped task path; absent, tasks run inline.
# REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379

# --- Server -----------------------------------------------------------------
# PORT=8023
